UML:TaggedValue.value: Application Schema for soil sampling, soil specimens and related observations
Use the OM_Observation/resultQuality/ DQ_QuantitativeAttributeAccuracy attribute to represent analytical errors and detection limits for each analytical measurement.
A specialisation of SF_SpatialSamplingFeature to allow the depth at which the sample was taken and the size of the sample.
To specify the upper and lower depths that the sample was taken from

UML:TaggedValue.value: To describe related observations via the SoilSample feature.
9$ea_notes= Unique integer value for properties of the type used to sort properties (applies to ISO 19136:2007 encoding rule)

inlineOrByReference$ea_notes=Values: inline | byReference | inlineOrByReference Default: inlineOrByReference Description: Controls whether property values may be encoded inline or by reference (applies to ISO 19136:2007 encoding rule)
false$ea_notes=Values: true | false Default: false Description: Indicates whether the property is considered metadata about the instance - and not information about the phenomenon in the real world.

ANZSoilML model constraint: At least "nameOfMeasure" and "result" shall be used when delivering om:resultQuality/gmd:DQ_QuantitativeAttributeAccuracy. The characterString in "nameOfMeasure" should be a term from a controlled vocabulary

The geometry of SoilSample should be a 0D point, 1D profile or 2D polygon, not 3D volumes. Therefore the depthRange of the sample is specified rather than being included in the geometry property. Where a 3D geometry is provided the depthRange will duplicate the 3D geometry depth.
A specialisation of SF_Specimen to capture archived specimens. NatSoil archive indicates whether there is a coarse fraction (>2mm) present in the specimen.
Presence or absence of coarse fragment sample >2mm
